1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:57,090 --> 00:01:58,970
You raised your price again?!

3
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:03,930
Aren't you charging a bit too much?

4
00:02:05,730 --> 00:02:08,640
Raise it again and I'll stop buying it!

5
00:02:13,770 --> 00:02:16,310
What's the big deal?
It's just a paper or two.

6
00:02:16,310 --> 00:02:18,900
It's a big deal when you're
buying it every day!

7
00:02:19,340 --> 00:02:25,050
You know you don't need to save up now
that Arlong's gone from your village, right?

8
00:02:25,050 --> 00:02:27,350
You can stop obsessing
over money, too.

9
00:02:27,350 --> 00:02:28,590
Show's what you know!

10
00:02:28,590 --> 00:02:33,610
Now that everything's over,
I can save up for myself!

11
00:02:34,170 --> 00:02:38,050
I don't wanna be some poor
pirate who can't even dress up!

12
00:02:38,050 --> 00:02:40,230
Hey, easy there!

13
00:02:40,230 --> 00:02:43,350
I'm trying to make my
special Tabasco Star!

14
00:02:46,650 --> 00:02:49,520
An eyeful of this
will make any bad guy–

15
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:56,870
C'mon! Just one!

16
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:58,110
Water! Water! Water!

17
00:02:56,870 --> 00:02:58,110
No!

18
00:02:58,110 --> 00:03:00,800
This is Nami's tangerine orchard!

19
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:03,870
I won't let anyone lay a finger on it!

20
00:03:03,870 --> 00:03:06,910
Nami! Nothing will get past
my loving protection!

21
00:03:06,910 --> 00:03:09,080
Yeah. Thanks, Sanji.

22
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:13,170
She's got him wrapped
around her finger...

23
00:03:15,290 --> 00:03:19,300
C'mon! Just one tangerine!

24
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:20,710
Cheapskate Sanji.

25
00:03:20,710 --> 00:03:22,190
I said no!

26
00:03:23,310 --> 00:03:26,260
Oh, well! I'm pretty happy anyway!

27
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:33,210
The world's always so chaotic.
Another coup in Villa...

28
00:03:35,730 --> 00:03:37,150
A flyer?

29
00:04:09,330 --> 00:04:15,560
So, at the very least, they've become
too much for our branches to handle?

30
00:04:16,060 --> 00:04:17,150
Correct.

31
00:04:17,150 --> 00:04:19,410
Even before he had a crew,

32
00:04:19,410 --> 00:04:23,460
he took down a Marine branch
captain—Axe-Hand Morgan—

33
00:04:23,460 --> 00:04:26,700
and he's shown no signs
of slowing since.

34
00:04:27,370 --> 00:04:29,870
Buggy the Clown: 15 million.

35
00:04:29,870 --> 00:04:33,300
Pirate Fleet Commodore Don Krieg: 17 million.

36
00:04:33,300 --> 00:04:37,040
Fishman Pirate,
Saw-Tooth Arlong: 20 million.

37
00:04:37,450 --> 00:04:41,690
The average bounty in
the East Blue is 3 million belly,

38
00:04:41,690 --> 00:04:47,010
but these major pirates—each worth
more than 10 million—were taken down!

39
00:04:48,290 --> 00:04:52,680
It's globally unprecedented for
a bounty to start at thirty million belly,

40
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:55,350
but it's not so excessive
an amount, either.

41
00:04:55,350 --> 00:04:57,970
Seeds of villainy
must be nipped in the bud,

42
00:04:57,970 --> 00:05:00,820
before they have a chance
to blossom out of control.

43
00:05:03,170 --> 00:05:05,030
Absolutely.

44
00:05:07,470 --> 00:05:09,660
We're wanted criminals now!

45
00:05:10,150 --> 00:05:12,450
It says I'm worth 30 million belly!

46
00:05:13,990 --> 00:05:18,380
Look! I'm gonna be seen around
the world! Girls might fall for me!

47
00:05:18,380 --> 00:05:21,710
What?! They included
Long Nose but left me out?!

48
00:05:23,130 --> 00:05:26,090
Where are you?!
I don't see you at all!

49
00:05:26,090 --> 00:05:27,560
Right there!

50
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:32,130
It's just the back of your head.
It's nothing to brag about.

51
00:05:32,130 --> 00:05:33,810
Don't be so glum!

52
00:05:33,810 --> 00:05:37,310
If you turn enough heads, you'll get
one even without being a captain.

53
00:05:37,310 --> 00:05:38,330
Seriously?!

54
00:05:38,330 --> 00:05:40,520
Well, just keep trying!

55
00:05:42,770 --> 00:05:46,280
Let's hurry and get to
the Grand Line, you guys!

56
00:05:46,280 --> 00:05:51,400
Yet again, you guys are
missing how serious this is!

57
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:54,750
All of our lives are in danger now!

58
00:05:55,510 --> 00:06:00,420
This is no time to be taking it easy
and relaxing in the East Blue...

59
00:06:03,930 --> 00:06:06,140
Thirty million belly...

60
00:06:06,140 --> 00:06:08,790
Marine HQ is sure to act
on a number that high...

61
00:06:08,790 --> 00:06:11,680
and we'll be swarmed with
strong bounty hunters.

62
00:06:12,650 --> 00:06:15,690
They'll be a bigger challenge
than anyone we've faced!

63
00:06:19,770 --> 00:06:21,610
Miss!

64
00:06:24,130 --> 00:06:25,860
Miss Kaya!

65
00:06:26,830 --> 00:06:27,950
Miss!

66
00:06:27,950 --> 00:06:29,860
What's wrong, Merry?!

67
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:31,740
Have a look at this!

68
00:06:33,190 --> 00:06:34,540
Usopp!

69
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:39,810
That's definitely Usopp
facing the other way!

70
00:06:39,810 --> 00:06:42,460
Now that you mention it, you're right...

71
00:06:47,810 --> 00:06:48,880
Finally!

72
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:52,930
Luffy! You've taken the first step
toward your dream!

73
00:06:53,910 --> 00:06:57,890
I'm Luffy. The man who's
gonna be King of the Pirates!

74
00:07:01,270 --> 00:07:04,230
See ya!

75
00:07:04,230 --> 00:07:09,700
But the next time we meet,
we may be enemies!

76
00:07:43,290 --> 00:07:47,430
We're finally approaching
the Grand Line.

77
00:07:47,430 --> 00:07:51,240
There's a famous settlement
on this island... Loguetown.

78
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:53,200
Loguetown?

79
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:56,190
It's known as the Town of
Beginnings and Endings.

80
00:07:56,770 --> 00:07:58,830
Its reputation precedes itself.

81
00:08:00,270 --> 00:08:05,790
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates,
was born and executed in that town.

82
00:08:09,570 --> 00:08:11,830
The town where the King
of the Pirates died...

83
00:08:13,670 --> 00:08:14,760
Wanna go?

84
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:17,290
Yeah! I have to see it!

85
00:08:17,290 --> 00:08:19,680
The man who got the One Piece—

86
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:22,480
everything the world has to offer—

87
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:25,450
was born and then died there!

88
00:08:37,370 --> 00:08:40,780
Anyone who wants to flee
should do so now!

89
00:08:40,790 --> 00:08:42,710
This bastion of peace will not

90
00:08:42,710 --> 00:08:45,500
tolerate any weakness
during this age of piracy!

91
00:08:46,310 --> 00:08:50,780
The weak and the feeble are not
to blame! They will have justice!

92
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:53,050
If evil persists upon the seas,

93
00:08:53,050 --> 00:08:58,190
then we Marines must drive it
away with the utmost of force!

94
00:08:58,970 --> 00:09:01,520
In the name of absolute justice!

95
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:07,270
"Justice"

96
00:09:03,780 --> 00:09:05,090
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

97
00:09:07,290 --> 00:09:11,360
Wow! What a huge town!

98
00:09:11,980 --> 00:09:16,430
The place used to be full of pirates
on their way to the Grand Line.

99
00:09:16,430 --> 00:09:18,740
So it has everything you could need!

100
00:09:18,740 --> 00:09:22,170
Alright! Our next adventure
is going to be a big one,

101
00:09:22,170 --> 00:09:24,290
so I'll need get us some equipment.

102
00:09:24,630 --> 00:09:27,280
Looks like I can get some
good ingredients here.

103
00:09:27,280 --> 00:09:28,920
Good women, too!

104
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:31,030
There's something I wanna buy, too.

105
00:09:31,030 --> 00:09:33,180
Oh? How are you gonna do that?

106
00:09:33,180 --> 00:09:35,510
You're flat broke, as I recall!

107
00:09:35,510 --> 00:09:38,390
Alright! I'm gonna check
out the execution platform!

108
00:09:38,390 --> 00:09:38,890
– Huh?
– Huh?

109
00:09:39,370 --> 00:09:43,010
I'm gonna see where
the King of the Pirates was executed!

110
00:09:43,010 --> 00:09:46,410
Hey, wait! We haven't decided
where we're meeting up yet!

111
00:09:47,070 --> 00:09:49,650
Man, that guy...

112
00:09:51,970 --> 00:09:55,490
The King of the Pirates was
born here and died here!

113
00:09:55,490 --> 00:09:58,450
He might have walked
down this very street!

114
00:09:58,770 --> 00:10:00,490
Yahoo!

115
00:10:00,490 --> 00:10:04,450
Damn, these are expensive!
Too expensive!

116
00:10:04,450 --> 00:10:06,370
Lend you money?

117
00:10:06,370 --> 00:10:07,730
No problem!

118
00:10:07,730 --> 00:10:11,790
But after interest, you'll owe me
300 percent of what I lend you!

119
00:10:11,790 --> 00:10:15,010
I can't afford to borrow
any more from her...

120
00:10:15,010 --> 00:10:18,200
but I can't enter the Grand Line
with just one sword...

121
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:20,430
What do I do?

122
00:10:18,910 --> 00:10:20,430
"Monster"?! Now, that's just rude!

123
00:10:20,430 --> 00:10:20,980
Huh?

124
00:10:21,510 --> 00:10:23,270
Shut it!

125
00:10:23,270 --> 00:10:27,240
Our boss is behind
bars because of him!

126
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:28,530
Then learn from his mistake.

127
00:10:28,530 --> 00:10:29,940
That's rich!

128
00:10:29,940 --> 00:10:32,290
We ain't happy with things as they are!

129
00:10:32,290 --> 00:10:36,400
We're gonna let him see
your corpse when we drag it to him!

130
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:38,950
Very well. I will fight you.

131
00:10:38,950 --> 00:10:39,940
Will you now, girlie?!

132
00:10:39,940 --> 00:10:41,740
Don't make us laugh!

133
00:10:41,740 --> 00:10:44,200
What can a girl possibly do?!

134
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:44,780
Die!

135
00:10:44,780 --> 00:10:46,240
Yeah!

136
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:06,060
She did it!

137
00:11:06,060 --> 00:11:08,370
You're one tough lady!

138
00:11:08,370 --> 00:11:09,870
You're amazing!

139
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:16,030
I can't tell if she's strong or weak!

140
00:11:14,050 --> 00:11:18,360
Glasses... Glasses... Glasses...
Where are my glasses...?

141
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,670
My glasses...

142
00:11:19,670 --> 00:11:21,230
Hey. You looking for these?

143
00:11:23,620 --> 00:11:25,450
S-Sorry for the trouble!

144
00:11:27,410 --> 00:11:28,930
Thank you!

145
00:11:30,730 --> 00:11:31,270
How's this?

146
00:11:31,270 --> 00:11:33,630
Oh! You look wonderful, miss!

147
00:11:34,130 --> 00:11:34,640
How's this?

148
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:36,880
It's so elegant, miss!

149
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:37,400
And this?

150
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:39,000
Elemental, miss!

151
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:39,500
This one?

152
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:40,760
Electrical!

153
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:41,160
This?

154
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:42,340
Elegy!

155
00:11:42,850 --> 00:11:45,470
Will you be purchasing all of these?

156
00:11:45,470 --> 00:11:46,430
Nah, I don't want 'em.

157
00:11:46,430 --> 00:11:48,450
I want something a bit more rugged.

158
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:50,810
Come again!

159
00:11:51,140 --> 00:11:54,100
Oh! A top-quality aperitif!

160
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:57,610
Oh! Two Poinderine
champagne-like beauties!

161
00:11:57,950 --> 00:12:01,730
The whole town is brimming with
the finest ingredients around!

162
00:12:01,730 --> 00:12:05,660
Damn, I can't decide
what to go for first!

163
00:12:07,770 --> 00:12:10,290
I just found the main dish!

164
00:12:10,290 --> 00:12:12,540
"Love-Love Pirates"

165
00:12:12,850 --> 00:12:15,170
Awesome! What is this place?!

166
00:12:15,170 --> 00:12:17,710
Everything here is a collector's dream!

167
00:12:17,710 --> 00:12:19,130
Welcome!

168
00:12:19,580 --> 00:12:25,090
Everything here once belonged to pirates
who returned alive from the Grand Line!

169
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:28,100
These goods are especially valuable.

170
00:12:28,100 --> 00:12:32,560
Then all these items were used
during adventures in the Grand Line?!

171
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:34,690
That's absolutely correct!

172
00:12:34,690 --> 00:12:38,750
We only do business with
warriors of the sea here,

173
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:42,610
so it'll be my personal pleasure to
serve a gentleman such as yourself!

174
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:47,910
What do you say? This was
the favorite gun of the Gold Roger!

175
00:12:47,910 --> 00:12:50,610
What?! The Gold Roger?!

176
00:12:50,610 --> 00:12:51,610
Yes!

177
00:12:52,630 --> 00:12:55,030
How about it, sir?

178
00:12:55,030 --> 00:12:56,290
Sh-Show me more!

179
00:12:56,710 --> 00:12:58,420
Thanks! Come again!

180
00:13:01,610 --> 00:13:04,050
Where are we going exactly?!

181
00:13:04,490 --> 00:13:07,550
You broke my glasses.

182
00:13:08,270 --> 00:13:11,470
I told you. I'll pay
you back... somehow.

183
00:13:12,260 --> 00:13:14,900
You don't look like
you have any money!

184
00:13:14,900 --> 00:13:16,770
Something about you just seems off!

185
00:13:16,770 --> 00:13:19,800
T-True, I don't have any money, but...

186
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:21,540
Those wrinkles between your eyes!

187
00:13:21,540 --> 00:13:23,990
You look like you
haven't eaten for days!

188
00:13:24,550 --> 00:13:27,200
Is your mother sick?!

189
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:31,660
Did your wife run out on you, leaving
you to raise five kids on your own?!

190
00:13:31,660 --> 00:13:33,330
L-Listen, you!

191
00:13:33,330 --> 00:13:36,120
I don't need the details!
Just come with me!

192
00:13:41,050 --> 00:13:43,460
Th-The Marines?

193
00:13:45,490 --> 00:13:46,260
Here.

194
00:13:47,070 --> 00:13:51,140
If you work for the Marines, you'll
never need to worry about money!

195
00:13:51,140 --> 00:13:54,220
Screw that! Why should
I work for the Marines?!

196
00:13:54,610 --> 00:13:58,410
You're just going to take off?!
I'm trying to do you a favor here!

197
00:13:59,070 --> 00:14:00,310
Look, you...!

198
00:14:00,890 --> 00:14:03,130
Sergeant Major! It's time for training!

199
00:14:03,130 --> 00:14:05,440
Bye! Please work hard, okay?

200
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:07,200
Sergeant Major?!

201
00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:11,490
Damn it! I'm getting nowhere like this!

202
00:14:16,990 --> 00:14:18,960
Looks like three-mop style is best!

203
00:14:22,920 --> 00:14:24,130
Let me try again!

204
00:14:31,350 --> 00:14:32,890
You! What are you doing here?!

205
00:14:33,850 --> 00:14:36,670
I knew it! You're Pirate Hunter Zoro!

206
00:14:36,670 --> 00:14:38,850
Why the hell are you
in here cleaning?!

207
00:14:38,850 --> 00:14:43,270
Intel says you've joined
Monkey D. Luffy's crew!

208
00:14:43,270 --> 00:14:44,690
You're under arrest!

209
00:14:50,950 --> 00:14:54,450
Well... now what?

210
00:14:57,210 --> 00:14:58,750
What happened here?!

211
00:15:00,390 --> 00:15:03,710
It seems someone attacked them!
There's no trace of the assailant!

212
00:15:08,270 --> 00:15:09,550
"For your glasses."

213
00:15:14,390 --> 00:15:16,920
Man, that freaked me out...

214
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:19,610
Dammit! She looks
way too much like Kuina!

215
00:15:19,610 --> 00:15:22,550
Not to mention
she's a swordsman, too...

216
00:15:22,550 --> 00:15:26,150
The world sure is a big place,
but I doubt I'll ever see her again.

217
00:15:34,230 --> 00:15:35,490
I'd like some swords.

218
00:15:36,530 --> 00:15:40,860
Ah, yes! Welcome!
Browse to your heart's content!

219
00:15:40,860 --> 00:15:43,500
Our shop's been in business
for 200 years now!

220
00:15:44,990 --> 00:15:48,590
I have 100,000 belly.
Sell me two swords.

221
00:15:48,610 --> 00:15:51,410
What...? Two swords
for 100,000 belly?

222
00:15:51,410 --> 00:15:54,470
Damn, he's a bum.

223
00:15:56,090 --> 00:15:58,930
Fifty grand a sword will only
buy you some dull blades.

224
00:15:59,340 --> 00:16:02,440
I'll make do with whatever.
I just can't afford anything else.

225
00:16:02,870 --> 00:16:06,830
You'll make do with whatever?
Hmph! What an amateur!

226
00:16:08,130 --> 00:16:11,190
That sword on his waist!
Could it be...?!

227
00:16:11,190 --> 00:16:17,930
O-Oh, h-h-hold on. L-L-Lemme
see that sword of y-y-yours!

228
00:16:17,930 --> 00:16:19,950
What's got you all agitated?!

229
00:16:19,950 --> 00:16:21,330
J-Just let me see it!

230
00:16:21,330 --> 00:16:23,160
Weirdo.

231
00:16:24,870 --> 00:16:27,040
I-It's the real thing!

232
00:16:28,830 --> 00:16:31,790
C-Calm down! This is your chance!

233
00:16:31,790 --> 00:16:35,430
An absolute amateur just waltzed
right in here with a named blade!

234
00:16:35,430 --> 00:16:37,720
You need to play it cool!

235
00:16:38,390 --> 00:16:41,390
Wow, this is a nice sword
you've got here!

236
00:16:41,390 --> 00:16:45,030
What do you say? I can take it off
your hands for 200,000 belly.

237
00:16:45,030 --> 00:16:48,330
That'll net you a total
of 300,000 belly!

238
00:16:48,330 --> 00:16:51,740
You'll be able to buy three
decent blades at 100,000 apiece.

239
00:16:52,090 --> 00:16:54,150
Huh?! What're you talking about?!

240
00:16:54,150 --> 00:16:59,160
Oh, alright! I-I'll make it
250,000... No! 300,000!

241
00:17:00,530 --> 00:17:02,040
Then, 500,000...?

242
00:17:02,040 --> 00:17:05,000
Look. Raise the price all
you want, this sword isn't–

243
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:08,840
Alright, then! I'll buy it
from you for 650,000 belly!

244
00:17:09,830 --> 00:17:14,220
I get it! You're a pro!
How does 800,000 belly sound?!

245
00:17:14,220 --> 00:17:15,900
Hello!

246
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:18,300
Did you finish polishing my Shigure?

247
00:17:20,310 --> 00:17:22,470
Thank goodness! You're all right!

248
00:17:22,470 --> 00:17:27,010
Someone went on a rampage
at the Marine outpost earlier.

249
00:17:27,010 --> 00:17:29,770
You went missing, so I was worried!

250
00:17:29,770 --> 00:17:33,030
How dense can she be?

251
00:17:30,790 --> 00:17:33,030
Thank goodness! What a relief...

252
00:17:33,030 --> 00:17:35,950
But the fact that you're
here, safe and sound...

253
00:17:35,950 --> 00:17:39,990
means you must have scoffed
at my kind offer and ran off!

254
00:17:40,530 --> 00:17:42,530
Here, take your money back.

255
00:17:42,530 --> 00:17:45,540
I can't accept money
from someone that cold.

256
00:17:45,540 --> 00:17:48,450
Besides, I already bought
some new glasses!

257
00:17:51,170 --> 00:17:53,760
Don't tell me this sword
is the Wado Ichimonji!

258
00:17:54,950 --> 00:17:56,720
It has to be the Wado Ichimonji!

259
00:17:57,100 --> 00:17:58,300
Wado...?

260
00:17:59,230 --> 00:18:01,050
Don't say it! Don't say it!

261
00:18:02,970 --> 00:18:05,050
A beautiful straight temper line!

262
00:18:05,050 --> 00:18:07,730
I believe it's one of the
twenty-one great grade swords!

263
00:18:09,570 --> 00:18:14,960
See! Look at this! It's worth
no less than 10 million belly!

264
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:17,490
But how did you come
across a named blade?

265
00:18:17,490 --> 00:18:20,680
Dammit! You just had to go
and run your mouth!

266
00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:23,170
I'll sue for obstruction of business!

267
00:18:23,170 --> 00:18:24,990
O-Obstruction of business?

268
00:18:24,990 --> 00:18:27,960
I'm sorry! Did I say something wrong?

269
00:18:28,950 --> 00:18:31,340
You're here for Shigure, right?!

270
00:18:31,340 --> 00:18:33,880
I'm done polishing it!
Take it and get the hell out!

271
00:18:37,340 --> 00:18:39,850
Why did you run straight into those?!

272
00:18:39,850 --> 00:18:41,300
I-I'm sorry.

273
00:18:42,170 --> 00:18:44,550
That klutz saved you!

274
00:18:44,550 --> 00:18:47,940
Really though, a named blade
is wasted on a guy who

275
00:18:47,940 --> 00:18:49,980
wields it without knowing its value.

276
00:18:50,560 --> 00:18:53,930
All the swords in that barrel
are 50,000 belly apiece!

277
00:18:53,930 --> 00:18:55,950
Just pick whatever two you want!

278
00:18:56,570 --> 00:18:58,440
What's he so mad about?

279
00:18:58,770 --> 00:19:02,950
You must really like swords
to want to carry three of them!

280
00:19:02,950 --> 00:19:05,160
It reminds me of that
one bounty hunter!

281
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:06,970
A bounty hunter?

282
00:19:06,970 --> 00:19:09,570
He's very well-known.
His name is Roronoa.

283
00:19:09,570 --> 00:19:10,870
I hear that name a lot.

284
00:19:11,220 --> 00:19:15,150
Yes, he's known all
throughout the East Blue...

285
00:19:15,150 --> 00:19:16,450
but he's a demon!

286
00:19:16,450 --> 00:19:20,630
Using swords to hunt
bounties is unforgivable!

287
00:19:20,630 --> 00:19:23,410
Why has evil grown strong in this era?

288
00:19:23,950 --> 00:19:27,850
All the famous sword masters
are pirates or bounty hunters...

289
00:19:28,510 --> 00:19:31,690
And they possess the majority
of the world's named blades.

290
00:19:31,690 --> 00:19:33,480
It's a real shame...

291
00:19:35,870 --> 00:19:39,000
Well, everyone has their own
set of circumstances, right?

292
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:42,160
Every profession has to
keep up with the times somehow...

293
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:45,070
In any case, with my Shigure,

294
00:19:45,070 --> 00:19:47,830
I'm going to hone my swordsmanship

295
00:19:47,830 --> 00:19:52,050
and someday I'll retrieve all the named
blades from the criminals of the world!

296
00:19:52,770 --> 00:19:57,020
The twelve supreme grade swords,
the twenty-one great grade swords,

297
00:19:57,020 --> 00:20:00,130
and the fifty fine grade swords...
I'll risk my life for them!

298
00:20:00,990 --> 00:20:03,180
You gonna take this sword, too?

299
00:20:03,180 --> 00:20:04,840
The Wado Ichimonji, was it?

300
00:20:07,570 --> 00:20:10,810
That is... It's not that I want
the named blades for myself.

301
00:20:11,690 --> 00:20:14,770
I'm just saying I don't want
criminals to wield them!

302
00:20:19,470 --> 00:20:20,650
This sword...

303
00:20:21,750 --> 00:20:23,110
That sword! I think it's...

304
00:20:25,610 --> 00:20:28,170
I thought so! Kitetsu III!

305
00:20:28,170 --> 00:20:29,540
It's the Kitetsu III!

306
00:20:29,540 --> 00:20:33,000
Its predecessor, the Kitetsu II,
is a great grade sword,

307
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:36,450
and the Kitetsu I before that is
listed as a supreme grade sword!

308
00:20:37,810 --> 00:20:41,240
Mister! Is this sword
really only 50,000 belly?!

309
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:42,420
Y-Yeah...

310
00:20:42,890 --> 00:20:46,140
Incredible! The grade of this
sword is very respectable!

311
00:20:46,140 --> 00:20:48,300
That one! You have to buy that one!

312
00:20:49,690 --> 00:20:51,810
It normally goes for one million belly!

313
00:20:51,810 --> 00:20:54,340
It's an absolute no-brainer!

314
00:20:54,340 --> 00:20:56,150
N-No! I can't sell it!

315
00:20:56,580 --> 00:21:01,040
Well, sure! Selling this for 50,000
belly would be extremely odd!

316
00:21:01,040 --> 00:21:02,070
No, that's not it...!

317
00:21:12,070 --> 00:21:13,450
A cursed sword, huh?

318
00:21:15,070 --> 00:21:16,170
You knew?!

319
00:21:17,670 --> 00:21:19,920
No. I can just tell.

320
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:21,930
From their first incarnation,

321
00:21:21,930 --> 00:21:26,950
every Kitetsu has been outstanding,
but each of them carries a curse!

322
00:21:28,250 --> 00:21:29,980
Many famous master swordsmen

323
00:21:29,980 --> 00:21:33,310
have met tragic deaths after
taking up Kitetsu swords.

324
00:21:33,310 --> 00:21:37,490
Nowadays, you won't find a single
person willing to use a Kitetsu

325
00:21:37,490 --> 00:21:41,710
because they'll take you from this world
even if you use one unknowingly!

326
00:21:41,710 --> 00:21:46,780
I just wanna get rid of the thing,
but I'm afraid it'll curse me...

327
00:21:46,780 --> 00:21:50,020
I-I'm sorry! I had no idea it was
such a terrifying sword!

328
00:21:50,020 --> 00:21:51,970
I should've minded my own business!

329
00:21:54,530 --> 00:21:56,750
I like it! I'll take it!

330
00:21:57,770 --> 00:21:59,910
A-Are you a moron?! I can't sell it!

331
00:21:59,910 --> 00:22:03,710
If you die because of it,
then it'd be like I killed you myself!

332
00:22:03,710 --> 00:22:07,030
You're the moron! Just get the sale!

333
00:22:07,030 --> 00:22:08,580
Honey!

334
00:22:08,580 --> 00:22:10,010
Then let's do this.

335
00:22:10,710 --> 00:22:13,470
My luck, or this thing's curse?

336
00:22:14,090 --> 00:22:16,510
We'll find out which is stronger.

337
00:22:20,610 --> 00:22:21,520
You can't...!

338
00:22:23,520 --> 00:22:27,200
Stop! It's sharp enough
to take your arm off!

339
00:22:45,670 --> 00:22:46,880
I'll take it.

340
00:22:52,330 --> 00:22:54,350
Hey. Could you pick
another one for me?

341
00:22:56,290 --> 00:22:56,930
S-Sure...

342
00:22:56,930 --> 00:22:58,480
H-Hold it!

343
00:23:06,810 --> 00:23:09,030
With a black lacquered sheath...

344
00:23:09,950 --> 00:23:11,910
and its blade's uneven
temper pattern...

345
00:23:14,250 --> 00:23:16,620
The fine grade sword Yubashiri!

346
00:23:16,620 --> 00:23:21,370
My shop may not be much,
but this is the finest sword I own!

347
00:23:21,770 --> 00:23:24,840
I can't afford it. I already
told you, I got no money.

348
00:23:24,840 --> 00:23:28,920
Forget the money. And I don't
need any for the Kitetsu, either.

349
00:23:28,920 --> 00:23:31,450
I'm sorry for trying
to cheat you earlier.

350
00:23:32,030 --> 00:23:34,230
I've not seen the eyes of
a good swordsman in ages.

351
00:23:34,230 --> 00:23:36,220
They say the sword
chooses the owner.

352
00:23:36,220 --> 00:23:38,800
I'll be praying for your good fortune!

353
00:23:47,430 --> 00:23:50,190
I definitely feel more
at ease with three swords.

354
00:23:50,560 --> 00:23:51,900
Oh, what's this?

355
00:23:51,900 --> 00:23:55,510
Hard to believe a miser like you
gave away the family treasure.

356
00:23:55,510 --> 00:23:58,410
Can't a man entrust
another with his dream?

357
00:23:59,700 --> 00:24:01,770
And I dream of you
taking out the trash!

358
00:24:01,770 --> 00:24:02,920
Y-Yes, ma'am!

359
00:24:02,920 --> 00:24:06,380
It scared me so much
that I still can't stand up...

360
00:24:14,260 --> 00:24:15,710
What's that?

361
00:24:18,010 --> 00:24:18,940
Lemme see.

362
00:24:27,450 --> 00:24:29,780
Hawk Eye! What're you doing here?!

363
00:24:30,310 --> 00:24:33,710
Calm down. I have
no qualms with you.

364
00:24:33,710 --> 00:24:35,780
Where is your boss?

365
00:24:37,770 --> 00:24:42,080
Camping out on an island like this...
What a carefree man.

366
00:24:44,510 --> 00:24:48,380
B-B-Boss!

367
00:24:58,010 --> 00:25:01,060
I-I-It's Hawk Eye!

368
00:25:05,560 --> 00:25:09,450
Hey there, Hawk Eye.
This is unexpected...

369
00:25:10,230 --> 00:25:14,530
I'm not feeling my best right now...
Have you come looking to fight?

370
00:25:15,730 --> 00:25:18,230
I have no intention of
settling our grievances...

371
00:25:18,230 --> 00:25:20,490
now that you're missing your left arm.

372
00:25:22,210 --> 00:25:24,860
I encountered an interesting pirate...

373
00:25:24,860 --> 00:25:27,880
and was suddenly reminded
of a story you used to tell.

374
00:25:29,070 --> 00:25:33,300
A story about an interesting boy
from a certain small village...

375
00:25:34,260 --> 00:25:35,050
You don't mean...!

376
00:25:42,410 --> 00:25:44,730
So you've made it, Luffy!

377
00:25:47,430 --> 00:25:49,440
In that case, Hawk Eye...

378
00:25:52,210 --> 00:25:55,550
I can't just let you leave now.

379
00:26:01,330 --> 00:26:03,190
That so, Hawk Eye?!

380
00:26:03,190 --> 00:26:07,250
Okay! Drink up! Drink up!
Today's a celebration!

381
00:26:07,890 --> 00:26:09,380
Did you not have a hangover?

382
00:26:09,380 --> 00:26:11,870
Don't sweat it! It's a celebratory drink!

383
00:26:11,870 --> 00:26:13,360
C'mon, now! C'mon, now!

384
00:26:13,360 --> 00:26:16,930
Just gulp it straight down!

385
00:26:18,570 --> 00:26:21,050
You ain't half bad!
Let's drink! Let's drink!

386
00:26:21,050 --> 00:26:22,100
Yeah!

387
00:26:22,100 --> 00:26:23,350
But, wait! Boss!

388
00:26:23,350 --> 00:26:26,900
You said you felt sick 'cause
you drank too much before!

389
00:26:26,900 --> 00:26:30,460
You dolt! How could I not drink
on a joyous day like today!

390
00:26:30,460 --> 00:26:31,840
The sun's still up.

391
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:33,570
Don't sweat it!

392
00:26:34,290 --> 00:26:35,990
Let's throw a party!

393
00:26:40,990 --> 00:26:44,020
Hey! Luffy's a wanted man now!

394
00:26:44,020 --> 00:26:45,870
Good for him!

395
00:26:45,870 --> 00:26:48,950
Y'know, this village might just
produce a great pirate!

396
00:26:48,950 --> 00:26:50,420
That'd be great!

397
00:26:50,420 --> 00:26:53,270
Quiet, you knuckleheads!

398
00:26:53,270 --> 00:26:54,090
Mr. Mayor!

399
00:26:54,590 --> 00:26:58,050
What's so good about a criminal
coming from our village?!

400
00:26:58,050 --> 00:27:00,010
A toast!

401
00:27:01,970 --> 00:27:05,010
Honestly! Every last one of them...!

402
00:27:07,030 --> 00:27:10,140
Come on, Mayor!
Luffy looks so happy here!

403
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:12,770
A pirate's a pirate!

404
00:27:14,690 --> 00:27:17,320
I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!

405
00:27:17,730 --> 00:27:22,950
Sure, but it's his dream.
Does that worry you?

406
00:27:24,530 --> 00:27:27,780
His dream... or fate?

407
00:03:54,420 --> 00:03:58,460
Marine HQ
Operated by the
World Government

408
00:04:37,130 --> 00:04:46,010
Commander Brannew
Marine Headquarters

409
00:15:36,870 --> 00:15:43,500
Ipponmatsu
Weapons Merchant

410
00:25:46,560 --> 00:25:49,440
Captain "Red-Haired" Shanks
Red Hair Pirates
